  d. Claim authorship, co-authorship, or primary credit for the Software
     or any substantial portion of it.

"Substantially similar" means that a reasonable observer, comparing the two
addons side-by-side, would recognize the derivative as being primarily this
Software with cosmetic, naming, or trivial functional changes.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. FORKS (PERMITTED, WITH CONDITIONS)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
You MAY publish a public fork of the Software only if ALL of the following
are true:

  a. The fork uses a clearly different addon name AND a clearly different
     addon folder name. ("Wardrobe2", "Wardrobe-Enhanced", or any variant
     containing the string "Wardrobe" does NOT satisfy this requirement.)
  b. The fork's root README prominently (within the first screen of
     rendered content) states that it is derived from Wardrobe by
     Veronica-Vasilieva, and links to
     https://github.com/Veronica-Vasilieva/Wardrobe
  c. The fork preserves this LICENSE file and all attribution required
     by section 2.
  d. The fork does not present itself, in any store listing, README,
     in-game UI, or promotional material, as an original creation of
     its publisher.
  e. The fork is itself released under this license, or a license no
     less restrictive than this one, for the same set of protected
     behaviors (attribution, no rebranding, non-commercial).

